##South Korea has seen an outbreak of super-transmission, with 82 confirmed patients attending a thousand-person Church

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter of the paper, Liu Dong, intern, Dong Anqi

The outbreak of the new coronavirus in South Korea has suddenly accelerated.

On February 20,53 new cases were confirmed in South Korea, more than all confirmed cases in the past month combined. Friday morning, the South Korean Center for Disease Control and Prevention (KCDC) reported that an additional 52 confirmed cases, the current national cumulative confirmed has increased to 156 cases.

And all of this, and Daegu city, a "super-transmission event" has a direct link, South Korea's disease control authorities believe that at least 82 confirmed cases are related to the incident.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
South Korean epidemic prevention personnel disinfected in Daegu city

Super-propagation event

In just three days, South Korea's epidemic suddenly took place "earth-shaking" changes.

According to the www.thepaper.cn  , there was a zero increase in the number of newly confirmed cases in five days between December 12 and 17, and the 29th and 30th cases of unknown infection were first reported by the South Korean government on the 16th. On the 18th, the 31st case emerged, and the epidemic began to spiral out of control. In South Korea, 15 cases were confirmed on the 19th, 53 on the 20th and 52 on the 21st morning.

Of the 156 confirmed cases of new coronavirus infection in South Korea, 111 have occurred in North Gyeongsang Province and Daegu. At least 82 of these cases were linked to a church cluster infection in Daegu city. Another major cluster of infection is in a hospital in qingshangbei-cheongdao county. Currently, 16 people have been confirmed to have been infected, of whom 5 are nurses. The first death in South Korea occurred at the same hospital on March 20.

A 61-year-old woman from Taegu is the "31st case" that triggered the spread of the disease in communities in the city of Daegu and set off a chain reaction, according to the country's epidemic prevention department. She has not been abroad in the past three months and has no history of "clear contact" with high-risk individuals in the affected areas. She was treated for a car accident at the end of January with Seoul, who developed fever on Feb. 4 and was later hospitalized, but the infected person was on the move until she was diagnosed on Feb. 17, in particular, 4 visits to a local church to attend the activities of the meeting.

Zhang Zhihua, a chinese-south Korean lawyer who has been following the development of the South Korean epidemic, told the paper, "It took more than 10 days for the diagnosis to be confirmed because the South Korean medical authorities dismissed her as a person with common flu symptoms because they believed she had no history of travel to China or contact with people at high risk of the outbreak. "

The analysis was supported by a statement from the South Korean Ministry of Health and Prevention, as Buddha's warrior attendant, deputy head of the Department of Central Emergency Management, admitted at a press conference on the 20th that the new coronavirus outbreak had occurred outside the network, started spreading through the neighborhood.

The large-scale spread of the disease in Daegu city, or with the 31st case between the emergence of symptoms and confirmed the frequent activities.

According to Zhang, the case in the past two weeks, not only between Seoul and Daegu between, but also in Daegu city local to the company, a number of local hospitals, churches, hotels and other places crowded with people. Most worrying of all, she attended four meetings at a local church, two of them after symptoms appeared.

The church is at the centre of this "super-spreading event" . According to South Korean media reports, the church is a new religious organization founded in 1984, in Korean society is controversial, some people see it as an extremist group, and was rejected by the Orthodox Christian Church.

According to Zhang, the church has more than 1,000 members and its Sunday services last more than two hours. The congregation would sit on the floor in a relatively confined space, embracing each other's shoulders with both arms and singing. After the Party will be in coffee shops and restaurants and other places to gather frequently, such close contact, increased the possibility of infection and transmission of the virus.

South Korea's epidemic prevention department said it had obtained a list of 1,001 members of the church who had worshiped with the 31st patient on February 9 and 16, and was imposing home quarantine measures on them, and confirm by phone if any of these people are showing symptoms. As of the morning of the 21st, at least 90 people had developed symptoms and 57 remained uncontacted. The infection could spread further.

"from the position of the South Korean government, the situation in Daegu is quite serious. The South Korean government has done a good job of responding to the outbreak. However, due to the long and highly infectious nature of the Virus latency, and the special circumstances of the 31 cases, there is still the community transmission that the South Korean government fears most. Under the current circumstances, Daegu city may consider closing down the city in order to avoid further expansion of the epidemic,"Zhang said.

To do everything in our power to overcome the epidemic

On the morning of the 21st, South Korean Prime Minister Ting se-joon, while presiding over the expanded meeting of Central Emergency Management at the Seoul office building of the Central Government, said, daegu city and Qingdaojun of North Gyeongsang Province, which have seen a sharp increase in new coronavirus infections, will be designated as special management areas for infectious diseases and relevant measures will be taken immediately to prevent and control the epidemic.

Ding said the government would take special measures to prevent the disease in the area, providing beds and human and material support. With more than 100 confirmed cases in China and community-acquired infections in some areas, the focus of epidemic prevention will shift from preventing the virus from entering the country from abroad to preventing community-acquired infections in China, and every effort will be made to overcome the epidemic.

"We are in the midst of an unprecedented crisis, " Kwon young-jin, the mayor of the hard-hit city of Daegu, told a televised news conference Thursday, urging 2.5 million Daegu residents to limit or refrain from going out, to reduce and prevent the possibility of new coronary pneumonia.

He said all members of the Church would be fully tested and asked to stay at home and be separated from their families. Meanwhile, the city of Taegu has ordered the closure of all kindergartens and all schools are considering postponing the spring semester, which was due to start in early March.

Located in southeastern South Korea, Daegu is South Korea's fourth largest city, less than an hour and a half drive from the capital Seoul, with a population of about 2.5 million. According to Yonhap News Agency, since the 20th, Daegu city, originally bustling business circles, restaurants and streets, began to become less crowded, even empty, and many citizens put on masks and are far away, local netizens described the scene as "like a disaster movie. ".

To combat the spread of the virus, the city has taken measures to temporarily close public libraries and public institutions such as the Daegu High Court have temporarily blocked certain entrances to their compound and installed thermal cameras. A pop star concert scheduled for March 8 at the Daegu Stadium has been postponed or canceled.

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
